# Page Structure Convention

- Keep each route inside its own folder under `app/` with a colocated `page.tsx`.
- Use `sections/` and `components/` for route folders when page complexity justifies it.
- Prefer route-level components inside `app/<route>/components/` and page sections inside `app/<route>/sections/`.
- `page.tsx` should stay thin and primarily compose route sections.
- Shared primitives reused across many routes should live in `components/shared/`.
- Marketing sections share horizontal spacing via `@/lib/layout/sectionShell` (see `.cursor/rules/site-section-layout.mdc`).
- Shared sitewide layout primitives (for example navbar/footer) can remain under `components/layout/`.
